Viable PEDV was not detected in any of the treated samples when tested by virus isolation. Irrespective of temperature, all the disinfectants reduced the estimated amount of PEDV on qRT-PCR as compared to the positive control (Fig. 1
). None of the disinfectants were able to produce qRT-PCR results that were negative across all replicates (Table 2
); however, strong solutions of sodium hypochlorite (0.52%, 1.03% and 2.06%) and 0.5% oxidizing agent did produce several negative or nearly negative qRT-PCR test results (Fig. 1 and Table 2). Numerically, fewer qRT-PCR positive samples were detected at 37 °C (n
 = 18) than 4 °C (n
 = 27), or −20 °C (n
 = 27).
